{"session_id":"svc-1778744656274452722","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-14T07:44:17.10001144Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"opus","sticky":{"key_present":true,"assignment":"not_applicable","bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"resolved_harness":"claude","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"opus","work_dir":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-6cde5ffd-20260514T074410-18020d6f","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Too big if any holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across ~5+ files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children once more; third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260514T074410-18020d6f/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing child IDs, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a success. Do not mix implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260514T074410-18020d6f/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;`.ddx/executions/20260514T074410-18020d6f/no_changes_rationale.txt` must contain one:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` reject.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;To request orchestrator decomposition, add `orchestrator_action: decompose` alongside `status: open`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260514T074410-18020d6f/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260514T074410-18020d6f/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and project defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-6cde5ffd\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003eregistry: install default package from embedded package FS\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;  `ddx init` must install the default `ddx` package offline from embedded package content, using the same installer semantics as `ddx plugin install ddx`. Today the binary embeds a special skill-only tree instead of the default package layout.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE\u0026#xA;  cli/internal/registry/installer.go:20-185 only installs packages by downloading a GitHub tarball. cli/cmd/init.go:276-299 works around offline/default-package needs by separately copying embedded skills and then attempting `registry.InstallPackage(pkg, workingDir)`, which downloads package content and may fail offline. cli/Makefile:65-84 syncs `skills/ddx` into `cli/internal/skills/ddx` for `go:embed`, not a package-rooted `library/` tree. The plan requires `InstallPackageFromFS(pkg, sourceFS, projectRoot)` or equivalent embedded-package support rooted at the default package.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;  - Add an embedded default-package FS under the registry package, rooted at the package layout that will be copied from `library/`.\u0026#xA;  - Split package install entrypoints into remote, local-dir, and embedded-FS paths that share the same core manifest/mapping implementation.\u0026#xA;  - Preserve the existing `InstallPackage(pkg, projectRoot)` public wrapper as the remote path only if callers still need it during the migration.\u0026#xA;  - Add offline tests proving an embedded package install can create `.ddx/plugins/ddx`, `.agents/skills/ddx`, and `.claude/skills/ddx` without network.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;  - Rewriting `ddx init` to call the embedded package installer; a dependent bead owns the init call site.\u0026#xA;  - Moving the source skill tree into `library/skills/ddx`; a later bead owns the content move.\u0026#xA;  - Removing old embedded skill files before offline init is green.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PARENT + DEPS\u0026#xA;  Parent: ddx-6862f2ac. Depends on the registry mapping bead so embedded installs use the same mapping implementation.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. `TestInstallPackageFromFSHonorsManifestMappings` proves an embedded `fs.FS` rooted at a package directory reads `package.yaml` and applies root plus skill mappings.\u0026#xA;2. `TestInstallPackageFromFSInstallsDefaultDDxPackageOffline` proves the embedded default package can install `.ddx/plugins/ddx`, `.agents/skills/ddx`, and `.claude/skills/ddx` without invoking network download code.\u0026#xA;3. `TestInstallPackageFromRemoteUsesSharedCore` proves the remote entrypoint and embedded-FS entrypoint share the same skill mapping behavior for a fixture package.\u0026#xA;4. `cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/registry/... -run \u0026#39;TestInstallPackageFromFSHonorsManifestMappings|TestInstallPackageFromFSInstallsDefaultDDxPackageOffline|TestInstallPackageFromRemoteUsesSharedCore\u0026#39; -count=1` passes.\u0026#xA;5. `cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/registry/...` passes.\u0026#xA;6. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003earea:cli, area:plugins, area:skills, kind:feature, phase:2, plan-2026-05-13, spec:plan-2026-05-13-ddx-skill-package-layout\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-6862f2ac\" spec-id=\"plan-2026-05-13-ddx-skill-package-layout\" base-rev=\"b68117e879a36d4a57912011777b45a0501cadb5\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260514T074410-18020d6f\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cref id=\"plan-2026-05-13-ddx-skill-package-layout\" path=\"docs/helix/02-design/plan-2026-05-13-ddx-skill-package-layout.md\"\u003eDDx Skill Package Layout\u003c/ref\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","attempt_id":"20260514T074410-18020d6f","base_rev":"b68117e879a36d4a57912011777b45a0501cadb5","bead_id":"ddx-6cde5ffd","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260514T074410-18020d6f","correlation_id":"ddx-6cde5ffd:20260514T074410-18020d6f","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260514T074410-18020d6f/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"ff5a37fddd2617eadf618ee605e83eba48ec24b4ba399e20d9d09a992d36